find /search/path/ type -d -name folder-name-here

Or you can use the double qoutes:
find /search/path/ type -d -name "folder-name-here"

If you want to look on the root folder:

sudo find / type -d -name folder-name-here

You must run it with sudo

To find with case UNsensitve:

find $HOME -type d -iname "Documents"


You can also use the 'locate' command:

 locate -b '\folder2'

 or

 locate Downloads
